#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 4. Sīsapāvanavagga → siṃsapāvanavaggo (bj, pts1) | sīsapāpaṇṇavaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga"
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 31. Sīsapāvanasutta → siṃsapāsuttaṃ (bj) | siṃsapā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Sīsapāvanasutta"
msgstr "31. In a Rosewood Forest"

# The simsapa is identified with Dalbergia sissoo, known as “North Indian Rosewood”. Since they’re in north India, I think just plain “rosewood” will do fine.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.438"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: sīsapāvane → siṃsapāvane (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.31:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati sīsapāvane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambī in a rosewood forest."

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahetvā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha picked up a few rosewood leaves in his hand and addressed "
"the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.3"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.4"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "Which is more:"

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.5"
msgid ""
"yāni vā mayā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahitāni yadidaṃ upari "
"sīsapāvane”ti?"
msgstr "the few leaves in my hand, or those in the forest above me?”"

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.6"
msgid ""
"“Appamattakāni, bhante, bhagavatā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahitāni;"
msgstr "“Sir, the few leaves in your hand are a tiny amount."

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.7"
msgid "atha kho etāneva bahutarāni yadidaṃ upari sīsapāvane”ti."
msgstr "There are far more leaves in the forest above.”"

# Following PTS, and apparently all manuscripts except the Burmese, which have appamattakam akkhatam
msgctxt "sn56.31:1.8"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, etadeva bahutaraṃ yaṃ vo mayā abhiññāya anakkhātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, there is much more that I have directly known but have not "
"explained to you. What I have explained is a tiny amount."

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.9"
msgid "Kasmā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā anakkhātaṃ?"
msgstr "And why haven’t I explained it?"

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.10"
msgid ""
"Na hetaṃ, bhikkhave, atthasaṃhitaṃ nādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na "
"virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya "
"saṃvattati;"
msgstr ""
"Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual "
"life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.11"
msgid "tasmā taṃ mayā anakkhātaṃ."
msgstr "That’s why I haven’t explained it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.31:2.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ?"
msgstr "And what have I explained?"

msgctxt "sn56.31:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti mayā "
"akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti mayā akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī "
"paṭipadā’ti mayā akkhātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"I have explained: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘"
"This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to "
"the cessation of suffering’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.31:3.1"
msgid "Kasmā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ?"
msgstr "And why have I explained this?"

msgctxt "sn56.31:3.2"
msgid ""
"Etañhi, bhikkhave, atthasaṃhitaṃ etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ etaṃ nibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati;"
msgstr ""
"Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual "
"life. It leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, "
"awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn56.31:3.3"
msgid "tasmā taṃ mayā akkhātaṃ."
msgstr "That’s why I’ve explained it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.31:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.31:4.2"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
